com.tractrac.subscription.lib.impl.io

Class TypeControllerCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tractrac.subscription.lib.impl.io.TypeControllerCollection

  • public class TypeControllerCollection
extends java.lang.Object
    This class has list of TypeControllers, for which it can start and stop live and stored data retreival. It also takes care of collecting each of the individual stored data progresses into one.
    Version:
    3.0
    Author:
    Jan Marthedal Rasmussen

      • add

        Parameters:

      • remove

        public void remove(TypeController typeController)
        Removes an existing type controller from the collection.

        Automatically closes down live and stored data requests.

        Parameters:
        typeController - the type controller to remove

      • startLive

        public void startLive()
        Starts live data retrieval for all type controllers in the collection.

        If live data has not been enabled then this call has no effect.

      • startStored

        public void startStored()
        Starts stored data retrieval for all type controllers in the collection.

        If stored data has not been enabled then this call has no effect.

      • stopLive

        public void stopLive()
        Stops live data retrieval for all type controllers in the collection.
